43: // Virtual Host Discovery Service (VHDS) is used to dynamically update the list of virtual hosts for
44: // a given RouteConfiguration. If VHDS is configured a virtual host list update will be triggered
45: // during the processing of an HTTP request if a route for the request cannot be resolved. The
46: // :ref:`resource_names_subscribe <envoy_v3_api_field_service.discovery.v3.DeltaDiscoveryRequest.resource_names_subscribe>`
47: // field contains a list of virtual host names or aliases to track. The contents of an alias would
48: // be the contents of a ``host`` or ``authority`` header used to make an http request. An xDS server
49: // will match an alias to a virtual host based on the content of :ref:`domains'
50: // <envoy_v3_api_field_config.route.v3.VirtualHost.domains>` field. The ``resource_names_unsubscribe`` field
51: // contains a list of virtual host names that have been :ref:`unsubscribed
52: // <xds_protocol_unsubscribe>` from the routing table associated with the RouteConfiguration.
53: service VirtualHostDiscoveryService {
54:   option (envoy.annotations.resource).type = "envoy.config.route.v3.VirtualHost";
55: 
